1
00:00:00,001 --> 00:00:01,069
(Previously)
Did you change the cat food?

2
00:00:01,093 --> 00:00:03,561
Yes. Not only that, I
changed the litter too.

3
00:00:03,600 --> 00:00:05,003
But you know, cats are...

4
00:00:05,187 --> 00:00:06,649
I'm doing all this for a creditor like you.

5
00:00:06,673 --> 00:00:08,818
Why are they all hiding today?

6
00:00:08,930 --> 00:00:10,317
I think they're protesting.

7
00:00:10,870 --> 00:00:11,870
Jiro!

8
00:00:13,874 --> 00:00:14,691
Don't be so hard on yourself.

9
00:00:14,747 --> 00:00:15,899
You already did really well.

10
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:17,246
You got a bunch of them back.

11
00:00:17,319 --> 00:00:17,981
Lynx!

12
00:00:18,026 --> 00:00:19,026
Jiro's collar.

13
00:00:19,101 --> 00:00:20,101
Jiro!

14
00:00:20,730 --> 00:00:22,377
From now on, I promise.

15
00:00:22,461 --> 00:00:23,913
I'll take the best care of you all.

16
00:00:24,019 --> 00:00:25,907
…do everything the way Mom did.

17
00:00:26,130 --> 00:00:28,010
Can you all give me one more chance?

18
00:00:28,437 --> 00:00:31,094
I help you run this café,
and in return, I get to be the cats' dad.

19
00:00:50,817 --> 00:00:54,305
Finally, our son's putting
his good looks to good use.

20
00:00:54,881 --> 00:00:57,580
With that style, he must have landed
an executive job.

21
00:00:58,111 --> 00:01:01,351
Good, he can now stop living off his dad.

22
00:01:01,713 --> 00:01:03,917
What kind of executive
dresses so stylishly?

23
00:01:04,546 --> 00:01:06,946
I think he's got his eye on someone.

24
00:01:07,444 --> 00:01:09,516
Looks like we'll have
a grandchild to raise soon.

25
00:01:09,991 --> 00:01:10,991
Trust me.

26
00:01:11,498 --> 00:01:13,212
- He got himself a job.
- A sweetheart.

27
00:01:13,401 --> 00:01:14,592
- A job!
- A sweetheart!

28
00:01:14,664 --> 00:01:16,110
- I said a job!
- A sweetheart!

29
00:01:16,237 --> 00:01:17,343
- A job!
- A sweetheart!

30
00:01:17,373 --> 00:01:18,373
- A job!
- A sweetheart!

31
00:01:18,413 --> 00:01:19,413
- A job!
- A sweetheart!

32
00:01:19,475 --> 00:01:20,853
- A job!
- A sweetheart. Trust me.

33
00:01:20,933 --> 00:01:22,326
Knock if off, Pa and Ma.

34
00:01:22,403 --> 00:01:23,403
No need to argue over it.

35
00:01:23,532 --> 00:01:25,086
I'm starting a new job

36
00:01:25,999 --> 00:01:27,483
with my potential future sweetheart.

37
00:01:27,792 --> 00:01:30,186
Whoa. What job?

38
00:01:30,354 --> 00:01:31,565
With whom, son?

39
00:01:32,142 --> 00:01:34,694
Once it's official,
I'll introduce that person to you.

40
00:01:36,559 --> 00:01:37,818
Now, I've got to head to work.

41
00:01:38,104 --> 00:01:39,104
I don't want to be late.

42
00:01:39,244 --> 00:01:42,313
Okay. Work hard, son.

43
00:01:43,203 --> 00:01:44,434
Told you, he's got a job.

44
00:01:44,471 --> 00:01:45,313
A sweetheart.

45
00:01:45,379 --> 00:01:46,407
- A job.
- A sweetheart.

46
00:01:46,472 --> 00:01:47,582
- A job!
- A sweetheart!

47
00:01:47,629 --> 00:01:49,432
- I said, a sweetheart.
- No, a job.

48
00:01:49,611 --> 00:01:50,611
- A sweetheart!
- A job!

49
00:01:50,678 --> 00:01:51,623
- A sweetheart.
- A job!

50
00:01:51,669 --> 00:01:52,949
Trust me. He's got a sweetheart.

51
00:02:04,324 --> 00:02:05,324
Jumbo.

52
00:02:05,889 --> 00:02:06,889
What's up?

53
00:02:07,710 --> 00:02:09,120
You woke me up this early?

54
00:02:36,553 --> 00:02:40,369
Ugggh… Jumbo!

55
00:02:42,172 --> 00:02:43,471
Just a sec, Jumbo.
Jumbo.

56
00:02:43,593 --> 00:02:44,593
- Lynx.
- Jumbo.

57
00:02:44,655 --> 00:02:46,150
- Hey, Lynx!
- Oh!

58
00:02:47,784 --> 00:02:48,674
Catch him!

59
00:02:48,767 --> 00:02:49,567
Jumbo.

60
00:02:49,692 --> 00:02:50,692
Jumbo.

61
00:02:50,901 --> 00:02:51,901
Careful.

62
00:02:52,325 --> 00:02:53,708
Jumbo.
Why are you hiding in there?

63
00:02:53,899 --> 00:02:55,313
Hold on.
Hold him on.

64
00:02:55,531 --> 00:02:56,531
Jumbo.

65
00:02:56,717 --> 00:02:57,929
Why are you hiding in there?

66
00:02:58,414 --> 00:02:59,414
Jumbo.

67
00:02:59,482 --> 00:03:00,282
Stay put.

68
00:03:00,454 --> 00:03:01,454
Jumbo.

69
00:03:01,778 --> 00:03:02,778
Oi.

70
00:03:03,272 --> 00:03:04,272
Jumbo!

71
00:03:13,093 --> 00:03:14,379
- Jumbo!
- Hey, Jumbo!

72
00:03:28,102 --> 00:03:29,616
Come on, no sulking.

73
00:03:30,397 --> 00:03:32,443
Don't catch things like that again.

74
00:03:33,336 --> 00:03:36,070
Do you know what this little one of yours
brought me this morning?

75
00:03:36,934 --> 00:03:38,206
That means he loves you.

76
00:03:39,314 --> 00:03:42,308
Thanks for loving me,
but please don't show it that way.

77
00:03:47,023 --> 00:03:48,023
Wait, Lynx.

78
00:03:55,766 --> 00:03:56,855
There's still one cat left.

79
00:03:57,051 --> 00:03:58,085
No, I'm good.

80
00:03:59,037 --> 00:04:00,037
Come on.

81
00:04:00,069 --> 00:04:01,069
It's okay.

82
00:04:01,103 --> 00:04:01,903
Come on.

83
00:04:02,055 --> 00:04:03,213
I can do it myself.

84
00:04:36,090 --> 00:04:37,090
Jumbo.

85
00:04:37,642 --> 00:04:38,642
Jumbo, my boy.

86
00:04:39,365 --> 00:04:40,365
Jumbo.

87
00:04:41,476 --> 00:04:42,476
Jumbo~

88
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:44,200
"Cat for Cash"
(Episode 3)

89
00:05:53,660 --> 00:05:54,660
Luang Phor!

90
00:05:55,499 --> 00:05:56,779
May I give alms?

91
00:05:59,946 --> 00:06:01,020
Is there a temple around here too?

92
00:06:01,044 --> 00:06:03,677
Normally, he receives alms at the market,

93
00:06:03,750 --> 00:06:05,901
but the road's closed
for construction right now.

94
00:06:06,058 --> 00:06:08,023
I see. Please wait here a moment.

95
00:06:20,012 --> 00:06:21,705
Does your friend want to give alms too?

96
00:06:26,933 --> 00:06:28,117
There's an old saying…

97
00:06:28,444 --> 00:06:30,921
Making merit and giving alms together

98
00:06:31,385 --> 00:06:32,592
means being partners forever.

99
00:06:34,439 --> 00:06:37,421
I mean business partners.

100
00:06:39,142 --> 00:06:40,142
May you be blessed with

101
00:06:40,416 --> 00:06:44,827
long life, beauty, happiness, and strength.

102
00:06:45,585 --> 00:06:46,385
Come out.

103
00:06:46,428 --> 00:06:47,294
Come out here.

104
00:06:47,427 --> 00:06:48,427
Come on out.

105
00:06:48,562 --> 00:06:49,615
Come here.

106
00:06:49,775 --> 00:06:50,633
Come here.

107
00:06:50,751 --> 00:06:51,751
Come out.

108
00:07:06,093 --> 00:07:08,221
(Oppa, saranghaeyo.)

109
00:07:19,535 --> 00:07:20,535
I'm the new staff.

110
00:07:21,484 --> 00:07:24,584
Please guide me, Mr. Lynx.

111
00:07:37,430 --> 00:07:39,461
That's my perfume. You like it?

112
00:07:53,244 --> 00:07:55,184
There it is.

113
00:07:55,730 --> 00:07:57,818
Now I know why John Wick came over here.

114
00:07:58,904 --> 00:08:00,504
Your kid peed again.

115
00:08:01,222 --> 00:08:02,618
Don't frame my kid.

116
00:08:03,075 --> 00:08:04,306
He's a good boy.

117
00:08:04,943 --> 00:08:06,524
Maybe someone spilled something there.

118
00:08:06,888 --> 00:08:08,403
Then go smell it.

119
00:08:16,861 --> 00:08:19,090
Yeah, it's cat pee.

120
00:08:19,469 --> 00:08:22,369
John Wick, why didn't
you use the litter box?

121
00:08:26,482 --> 00:08:28,984
Did you change the cat's stuff again?

122
00:08:29,638 --> 00:08:30,838
It seems like another protest.

123
00:08:31,798 --> 00:08:32,798
Change what?

124
00:08:33,086 --> 00:08:34,415
Stop blaming me already.

125
00:08:36,375 --> 00:08:37,938
Your kid is a good boy, right?

126
00:08:38,941 --> 00:08:40,726
You're his dad, so you clean it up.

127
00:08:50,285 --> 00:08:54,696
(It's strange. John
Wick is never like this.)

128
00:08:54,867 --> 00:08:57,631
(Maybe he's sick.)

129
00:09:03,090 --> 00:09:05,419
My mom used to make me
come here a few times.

130
00:09:06,989 --> 00:09:08,115
Then I stopped coming.

131
00:09:08,267 --> 00:09:09,067
Why?

132
00:09:09,185 --> 00:09:10,521
Uncle Vet here is scary.

133
00:09:10,836 --> 00:09:13,016
Not just cats, even I'm scared.

134
00:09:17,149 --> 00:09:20,210
Anyone who dares scare my kids
will have to go through me first.

135
00:09:21,050 --> 00:09:22,596
Here, if the cats behave,

136
00:09:23,520 --> 00:09:24,840
the vet won't be harsh with them.

137
00:09:29,759 --> 00:09:31,069
Hey, Dr. Pom.

138
00:09:32,463 --> 00:09:34,050
Hey, Lynx.

139
00:09:35,128 --> 00:09:37,676
Hey… who is he?

140
00:09:55,968 --> 00:09:56,968
All done.

141
00:09:57,690 --> 00:10:00,029
By the way, sorry I couldn't make it
to your mom's funeral.

142
00:10:00,133 --> 00:10:02,318
I was still studying overseas then.

143
00:10:02,459 --> 00:10:04,204
It's totally fine, Dr. Pom.

144
00:10:04,770 --> 00:10:06,201
I only just found out

145
00:10:06,510 --> 00:10:08,406
you took over your dad's vet clinic.

146
00:10:08,843 --> 00:10:11,323
Part of it is I was always
at your mom's café when I was a kid.

147
00:10:11,949 --> 00:10:13,815
When I saw the cats sick
and not feeling well,

148
00:10:14,216 --> 00:10:16,661
I wanted to do something
to help them recover and live longer.

149
00:10:17,247 --> 00:10:18,247
In the end,

150
00:10:18,694 --> 00:10:21,536
we both ended up as the second generation
running our family businesses.

151
00:10:22,801 --> 00:10:23,801
That's true.

152
00:10:24,674 --> 00:10:25,674
Sorry.

153
00:10:26,554 --> 00:10:28,212
Let me interrupt the reunion a bit.

154
00:10:29,639 --> 00:10:31,608
So what's wrong?

155
00:10:33,431 --> 00:10:34,231
Who?

156
00:10:34,417 --> 00:10:35,610
John Wick, of course.

157
00:10:35,819 --> 00:10:36,903
I mean you.

158
00:10:37,182 --> 00:10:38,182
Who are you?

159
00:10:40,762 --> 00:10:43,918
Ah, this is… Tiger.

160
00:10:44,489 --> 00:10:45,907
- He's…
- Lynx's business partner.

161
00:10:46,087 --> 00:10:50,101
But you don't look like an animal person.

162
00:10:51,897 --> 00:10:52,897
I like cats.

163
00:10:53,819 --> 00:10:54,819
I don't like dogs,

164
00:10:55,986 --> 00:10:57,243
especially Pom…eranians.

165
00:10:58,969 --> 00:10:59,969
Can I have your number?

166
00:11:02,198 --> 00:11:03,916
So we can stay in touch 24/7 if needed.

167
00:11:05,605 --> 00:11:06,605
Sure.

168
00:11:09,582 --> 00:11:12,199
Here. That's my personal number.

169
00:11:12,755 --> 00:11:14,877
It should be easier to reach me
than the café number.

170
00:11:15,022 --> 00:11:16,022
I've sent you my contact.

171
00:11:16,128 --> 00:11:17,351
That's my personal number too.

172
00:11:17,535 --> 00:11:18,335
Okay.

173
00:11:18,516 --> 00:11:19,516
Doc!

174
00:11:22,529 --> 00:11:23,619
Can I have your number too?

175
00:11:24,507 --> 00:11:25,810
The clinic number is over there.

176
00:11:26,217 --> 00:11:28,817
Please call during business hours only.

177
00:11:31,244 --> 00:11:32,510
Thank you for today, Dr. Pom.

178
00:11:33,455 --> 00:11:34,615
Do your best with the café.

179
00:11:35,296 --> 00:11:36,401
You've got my support here.

180
00:11:48,892 --> 00:11:50,912
Soft food, give medicine, monitor.

181
00:11:51,183 --> 00:11:53,207
Soft food, give medicine, monitor.

182
00:11:53,826 --> 00:11:55,915
Soft food, give medicine, monitor.

183
00:11:56,201 --> 00:11:57,984
Soft food, give medicine, monitor.

184
00:11:58,344 --> 00:12:00,436
Soft food, give medicine, monitor.

185
00:12:00,521 --> 00:12:01,715
Hey, Lynx.

186
00:12:02,922 --> 00:12:04,557
Have you ever given cat medicine before?

187
00:12:06,715 --> 00:12:07,801
What? Come on.

188
00:12:08,101 --> 00:12:09,943
It's just making him
take his medicine, right?

189
00:12:10,685 --> 00:12:12,616
I can just mix it into food.

190
00:12:13,413 --> 00:12:14,830
If it were that easy,

191
00:12:15,921 --> 00:12:17,310
cats wouldn't be ruling the world.

192
00:12:19,797 --> 00:12:21,395
You have to pry his mouth open,

193
00:12:21,971 --> 00:12:23,099
and pop the pill in.

194
00:12:26,349 --> 00:12:27,367
Pry his mouth open?

195
00:12:31,930 --> 00:12:32,930
Easy-peasy.

196
00:12:34,029 --> 00:12:36,209
Just get his mouth open.

197
00:12:37,521 --> 00:12:39,899
But I should trim his nails first,

198
00:12:40,615 --> 00:12:41,747
just to be safe.

199
00:12:55,286 --> 00:12:56,286
Come here.

200
00:12:58,190 --> 00:12:59,590
- (Don't you dare touch me!)
- Ouch!

201
00:12:59,650 --> 00:13:00,650
Lynx!

202
00:13:01,342 --> 00:13:02,342
You okay?

203
00:13:13,074 --> 00:13:14,074
I'm okay.

204
00:13:16,315 --> 00:13:19,115
I should wait until he's in a better mood.

205
00:13:19,616 --> 00:13:20,856
I'll give medicine to him then.

206
00:13:23,756 --> 00:13:24,756
Are you sure

207
00:13:25,724 --> 00:13:26,724
you can handle it alone?

208
00:13:31,064 --> 00:13:34,604
Want me to stay and help tonight?

209
00:13:36,614 --> 00:13:38,294
You can't even touch him.

210
00:13:39,245 --> 00:13:40,245
Just go home.

211
00:13:40,399 --> 00:13:41,406
I've got this.

212
00:13:46,798 --> 00:13:47,926
Can I have your number?

213
00:13:49,268 --> 00:13:50,518
Just in case something happens.

214
00:13:51,882 --> 00:13:53,103
Didn't you already have it?

215
00:13:54,786 --> 00:13:55,904
That's the café number.

216
00:13:57,654 --> 00:13:58,724
I want your number.

217
00:14:00,969 --> 00:14:01,969
Or…

218
00:14:03,130 --> 00:14:04,507
do I have to become a vet first

219
00:14:05,794 --> 00:14:07,043
for you to give me your number?

220
00:14:17,060 --> 00:14:18,060
Hey!

221
00:14:25,567 --> 00:14:26,567
Here.

222
00:14:27,347 --> 00:14:28,347
That's my number.

223
00:14:29,423 --> 00:14:30,520
You can call me anytime,

224
00:14:31,615 --> 00:14:32,744
no business hours.

225
00:14:41,631 --> 00:14:42,631
I'm heading out now.

226
00:15:08,640 --> 00:15:10,671
CAT DAD

227
00:15:17,836 --> 00:15:19,312
So what exactly do you do?

228
00:15:19,673 --> 00:15:22,019
Maybe I can give you advice.

229
00:15:25,112 --> 00:15:26,112
I'm in the…

230
00:15:27,859 --> 00:15:32,496
food and drinks sales business, Pa.

231
00:15:32,979 --> 00:15:34,218
Did you open a restaurant?

232
00:15:34,533 --> 00:15:35,809
Not exactly.

233
00:15:36,564 --> 00:15:38,203
What makes it more special is

234
00:15:38,876 --> 00:15:40,698
having staff to entertain customers.

235
00:15:41,425 --> 00:15:43,566
So, you've got like hosts and hostesses

236
00:15:43,736 --> 00:15:45,181
and customers pay for their company?

237
00:15:45,340 --> 00:15:46,340
Yes, Pa.

238
00:15:46,570 --> 00:15:48,603
The more they pay,

239
00:15:49,173 --> 00:15:50,821
the more staff will tend to them.

240
00:15:51,374 --> 00:15:54,103
Ahhh, I get it now.

241
00:15:54,686 --> 00:15:55,745
This is the kind of place

242
00:15:55,818 --> 00:15:56,886
I go and pay a lot at too.

243
00:16:00,704 --> 00:16:02,753
Uh I mean…

244
00:16:03,032 --> 00:16:04,801
before I met your mom.

245
00:16:07,298 --> 00:16:09,637
Places like this aren't hard to run.

246
00:16:10,169 --> 00:16:11,169
If you have time,

247
00:16:11,466 --> 00:16:13,451
I can train you and
walk you through everything.

248
00:16:15,398 --> 00:16:16,518
Thank you, Pa.

249
00:16:18,311 --> 00:16:19,943
I'll go shower now.

250
00:16:20,132 --> 00:16:21,132
OK.

251
00:16:25,173 --> 00:16:26,546
Let's get you medicine, John Wick.

252
00:16:31,680 --> 00:16:35,149
CAT DAD

253
00:16:41,423 --> 00:16:43,271
Couldn't you think of a better
name to save yourself as?

254
00:16:44,569 --> 00:16:45,569
Why?

255
00:16:45,729 --> 00:16:48,221
You let me be the dad
of all the cats at your café.

256
00:16:50,566 --> 00:16:52,700
If there's nothing else,
I'm hanging up.

257
00:16:53,561 --> 00:16:54,591
Hold on.

258
00:16:56,888 --> 00:16:58,014
I want to see the face.

259
00:17:01,299 --> 00:17:02,400
Can you turn the camera on?

260
00:17:04,722 --> 00:17:05,979
I'm not comfortable doing that.

261
00:17:07,233 --> 00:17:08,575
I didn't mean your face.

262
00:17:09,909 --> 00:17:11,441
I want to see John Wick.

263
00:17:21,369 --> 00:17:23,836
"I'm fine. I don't feel like eating,"

264
00:17:24,113 --> 00:17:25,633
"but I feel better than this morning."

265
00:17:26,367 --> 00:17:28,134
Did Papa scold you, John Wick?

266
00:17:28,548 --> 00:17:29,684
No, I didn't. Come on.

267
00:17:29,819 --> 00:17:31,602
It's your kid who keeps
hissing at me. Look.

268
00:17:31,690 --> 00:17:32,810
No, John Wick.

269
00:17:33,363 --> 00:17:34,363
I've got to go now.

270
00:17:34,486 --> 00:17:35,958
I'm giving him his medicine now.

271
00:17:36,073 --> 00:17:37,073
Wait, Lynx.

272
00:17:38,383 --> 00:17:39,511
Let me watch too.

273
00:17:40,693 --> 00:17:41,809
I'm rooting for you here.

274
00:17:44,038 --> 00:17:45,113
What do you want to watch?

275
00:17:45,320 --> 00:17:46,807
This is not a crocodile show.

276
00:17:49,179 --> 00:17:50,420
Come on, John Wick.

277
00:17:52,754 --> 00:17:54,236
Here you are.

278
00:17:54,881 --> 00:17:56,481
Swallow it. Come on.
Swallow it.

279
00:17:56,975 --> 00:17:57,975
(Let go of me!)

280
00:17:58,074 --> 00:17:59,074
- John Wick!
- Ouch!

281
00:17:59,251 --> 00:18:00,051
Lynx.

282
00:18:00,224 --> 00:18:01,224
Lynx!

283
00:18:01,285 --> 00:18:02,285
Lynx!

284
00:18:07,857 --> 00:18:08,857
Hey!

285
00:18:13,868 --> 00:18:14,868
Are you okay?

286
00:18:14,932 --> 00:18:15,932
I'm fine.

287
00:18:16,434 --> 00:18:17,844
You should be worrying about John Wick.

288
00:18:17,868 --> 00:18:20,009
If he doesn't take his medicine,
he won't get better.

289
00:18:23,166 --> 00:18:25,824
I'll hold John Wick

290
00:18:26,784 --> 00:18:27,816
and you pop in the pill.

291
00:18:27,896 --> 00:18:29,204
What about your allergy?

292
00:18:29,497 --> 00:18:30,497
I'll do it myself.

293
00:18:31,238 --> 00:18:32,238
Don't worry about it.

294
00:18:34,483 --> 00:18:35,483
John Wick, my boy.

295
00:18:35,693 --> 00:18:36,693
John Wick.

296
00:18:38,322 --> 00:18:39,415
There, there.

297
00:18:39,881 --> 00:18:41,164
Your daddy is here.

298
00:18:42,907 --> 00:18:44,126
Don't be scared, John Wick.

299
00:18:44,296 --> 00:18:46,923
There, there. You'll be okay.

300
00:18:49,289 --> 00:18:50,597
Good boy, John Wick.

301
00:18:52,473 --> 00:18:53,513
There you go.

302
00:18:54,858 --> 00:18:55,858
Good boy.

303
00:18:56,429 --> 00:18:57,429
You can go.

304
00:19:02,584 --> 00:19:03,584
How's it going?

305
00:19:05,050 --> 00:19:06,606
John Wick had his medicine.

306
00:19:07,122 --> 00:19:08,225
He should get better soon.

307
00:19:08,405 --> 00:19:09,521
I meant you.

308
00:19:09,985 --> 00:19:10,985
How are you holding up?

309
00:19:11,284 --> 00:19:12,284
Any reaction?

310
00:19:15,827 --> 00:19:17,106
Just a little itchy.

311
00:19:40,552 --> 00:19:41,552
I'm okay now.

312
00:19:42,245 --> 00:19:45,190
If it gets bad, my eyes will turn red,

313
00:19:45,251 --> 00:19:47,402
and won't stop tearing up.

314
00:20:03,838 --> 00:20:04,838
They don't look red yet.

315
00:20:10,798 --> 00:20:11,921
I'm really fine.

316
00:20:12,834 --> 00:20:13,834
What about you?

317
00:20:14,281 --> 00:20:15,321
Are you okay?

318
00:20:16,910 --> 00:20:17,910
Your face is red.

319
00:20:19,050 --> 00:20:20,985
No. I'm okay.

320
00:20:22,673 --> 00:20:23,815
I'm serious.

321
00:20:24,716 --> 00:20:25,716
Do you have a fever?

322
00:20:31,655 --> 00:20:34,164
I knew it. You're burning up.

323
00:20:35,161 --> 00:20:36,161
What did you do?

324
00:20:42,166 --> 00:20:43,189
Maybe…

325
00:20:45,570 --> 00:20:47,575
from bathing Jumbo this morning.

326
00:21:03,351 --> 00:21:04,351
Just put it there.

327
00:21:04,986 --> 00:21:05,986
I'll eat it later.

328
00:21:08,196 --> 00:21:09,876
Get up. I'll help you.

329
00:22:02,417 --> 00:22:03,827
- Take your shirt off.
- Huh?

330
00:22:08,402 --> 00:22:11,093
You're not in shape to take a shower.

331
00:22:11,827 --> 00:22:12,930
I'll wipe you down.

332
00:22:16,161 --> 00:22:17,380
No need.

333
00:22:23,341 --> 00:22:25,739
Then don't complain
when the kids don't listen to you.

334
00:22:27,481 --> 00:22:29,560
Fine, I got it.

335
00:22:30,363 --> 00:22:31,363
I'll do it myself.

336
00:23:16,659 --> 00:23:17,659
I'm done.

337
00:23:24,293 --> 00:23:25,403
Get some rest.

338
00:23:25,621 --> 00:23:26,824
Don't worry about the cats.

339
00:23:27,768 --> 00:23:28,768
How can I?

340
00:23:28,973 --> 00:23:31,493
- What if John Wick gets w—
- I'll keep an eye on him all night.

341
00:23:34,333 --> 00:23:35,495
I'm staying here tonight.

342
00:23:58,941 --> 00:24:01,922
(Are you gonna be okay
sleeping here with us?)

343
00:24:02,056 --> 00:24:03,196
I'm gonna be fine, Jiro.

344
00:24:03,693 --> 00:24:05,185
I already took allergy medicine.

345
00:24:07,216 --> 00:24:10,027
But can you please
keep your distance, okay?

346
00:24:10,173 --> 00:24:12,019
(Okidoki. Got it.)

347
00:24:16,631 --> 00:24:17,991
Does anyone know…

348
00:24:19,173 --> 00:24:21,637
why John Wick doesn't like
people getting close to him?

349
00:24:21,699 --> 00:24:22,912
(Jumbo doesn't know.)

350
00:24:22,985 --> 00:24:25,488
(But Jumbo knows
he already got his balls removed.)

351
00:24:25,644 --> 00:24:27,367
(Jumbo wants to have my balls removed too.)

352
00:24:27,482 --> 00:24:28,752
(That would be so cool.)

353
00:24:28,838 --> 00:24:31,118
(John Wick doesn't
really talk about himself.)

354
00:24:31,324 --> 00:24:34,419
(I heard he used to be a spy cat.)

355
00:24:34,628 --> 00:24:38,081
(But he knew too much and got hunted down.)

356
00:24:38,405 --> 00:24:40,210
(So he fled and came to live with Je Meow.)

357
00:24:40,284 --> 00:24:41,304
(That's nonsense.)

358
00:24:41,565 --> 00:24:43,477
(John Wick was an assassin cat.)

359
00:24:43,799 --> 00:24:46,532
(He once took someone out with a pencil.)

360
00:24:48,652 --> 00:24:50,800
Why does that sound like
a movie I've seen before?

361
00:24:51,949 --> 00:24:54,281
- So which is it, exactly?
- (Ahem. Be quiet. I'm trying to sleep here.)

362
00:24:54,305 --> 00:24:55,690
(Um… I'm going to bed now.)

363
00:24:55,715 --> 00:24:57,684
(Make sure you keep all the pencils away.)

364
00:25:03,705 --> 00:25:04,796
I don't think I can sleep

365
00:25:05,647 --> 00:25:09,415
knowing I'm leaving someone allergic
to cats to watch over the cats alone.

366
00:25:37,072 --> 00:25:38,072
At first,

367
00:25:39,704 --> 00:25:43,606
I thought it'd be the cats
who couldn't sleep.

368
00:25:45,453 --> 00:25:47,493
My mom used to sleep in here
with them all the time.

369
00:25:48,537 --> 00:25:49,910
Especially when one was sick,

370
00:25:50,534 --> 00:25:51,743
she'd hold that cat all night.

371
00:25:53,754 --> 00:25:54,754
That's nice.

372
00:25:55,920 --> 00:25:56,920
When I was a kid,

373
00:25:57,808 --> 00:26:02,082
if I got sick, my mom would just
drag me off to get shots.

374
00:26:02,543 --> 00:26:05,318
Only with the cats, though.
She never hugged me.

375
00:26:08,810 --> 00:26:10,298
Even when I was at the top of my class,

376
00:26:11,129 --> 00:26:13,094
she'd just listen while scooping litter.

377
00:26:24,698 --> 00:26:26,317
Who would dare hug you?

378
00:26:27,535 --> 00:26:29,517
You don't even let people touch you.

379
00:26:32,916 --> 00:26:34,416
Even cats choose

380
00:26:36,333 --> 00:26:38,016
who they let touch them, right?

381
00:26:39,804 --> 00:26:40,844
Like Dr. Pom?

382
00:26:48,104 --> 00:26:49,104
I mean…

383
00:26:50,628 --> 00:26:53,317
John Wick let Dr. Pom touch him.

384
00:26:55,080 --> 00:26:58,112
Do you know cats copy their owners?

385
00:27:00,301 --> 00:27:01,687
What does that have to do with me?

386
00:27:01,762 --> 00:27:03,523
You're friendly with Dr. Pom,

387
00:27:04,125 --> 00:27:05,484
so John Wick is too.

388
00:27:05,579 --> 00:27:06,703
So you're saying,

389
00:27:07,584 --> 00:27:09,303
if I want to give John Wick his medicine,

390
00:27:09,932 --> 00:27:11,446
I should let you pry my mouth open?

391
00:27:12,637 --> 00:27:15,611
Well, we don't need to go that far.

392
00:27:16,797 --> 00:27:20,403
Just try to ease into physical touch.

393
00:27:23,158 --> 00:27:24,220
Start with…

394
00:27:26,117 --> 00:27:27,317
scratching my back.

395
00:27:30,220 --> 00:27:32,050
The allergy medicine's wearing off.

396
00:27:34,184 --> 00:27:35,810
You're totally using that as an excuse.

397
00:27:36,945 --> 00:27:38,414
You just want to use me to do that.

398
00:27:40,624 --> 00:27:41,993
Ow, so itchy.

399
00:27:50,833 --> 00:27:51,833
Here?

400
00:27:55,086 --> 00:27:56,086
Ouch!

401
00:27:58,724 --> 00:28:02,014
It isn't just the cats,
your nails are long too.

402
00:28:13,843 --> 00:28:14,843
Lynx.

403
00:28:15,143 --> 00:28:16,143
Lynx.

404
00:28:17,187 --> 00:28:18,187
I'm just kidding.

405
00:28:38,012 --> 00:28:39,106
Trim my nails for me.

406
00:28:47,593 --> 00:28:48,818
I want to see

407
00:28:49,741 --> 00:28:51,387
if cats really copy their owners.

408
00:29:01,482 --> 00:29:04,202
Well then. May I?

409
00:30:00,238 --> 00:30:01,238
Did that hurt?

410
00:30:02,747 --> 00:30:04,718
No. I'm just sleepy.

411
00:32:19,231 --> 00:32:20,231
I…

412
00:32:21,168 --> 00:32:22,718
I'll go feed the cats first.

413
00:32:42,083 --> 00:32:43,083
Look!

414
00:32:45,287 --> 00:32:46,604
John Wick's eating now.

415
00:32:47,254 --> 00:32:48,616
The medicine must be working.

416
00:32:49,232 --> 00:32:50,285
That's a relief.

417
00:32:50,963 --> 00:32:52,003
Alright then,

418
00:32:53,157 --> 00:32:54,623
I'm going home to shower.

419
00:32:57,904 --> 00:32:58,904
Hey.

420
00:32:59,279 --> 00:33:00,279
Hm?

421
00:33:02,149 --> 00:33:03,803
You can shower here if you don't mind.

422
00:33:10,055 --> 00:33:11,306
I'll lend you some clothes.

423
00:33:21,021 --> 00:33:22,180
You don't feel hot anymore.

424
00:33:24,079 --> 00:33:25,330
Why are you being nice to me?

425
00:33:27,901 --> 00:33:30,428
W…well, you're helping with the cats.

426
00:33:31,033 --> 00:33:33,321
Why? Do you prefer me
raising my voice at you?

427
00:33:34,381 --> 00:33:35,381
Happy now?

428
00:33:42,749 --> 00:33:45,311
The Cold Prince is here.

429
00:33:47,033 --> 00:33:48,676
Hey, Tiger.

430
00:33:49,054 --> 00:33:51,003
Why are you here so early?

431
00:33:52,136 --> 00:33:53,597
I'm not early, Krapor.

432
00:33:53,987 --> 00:33:55,197
I just haven't gone home yet.

433
00:33:55,379 --> 00:33:56,379
What?

434
00:33:56,845 --> 00:33:58,523
You stayed over?

435
00:34:00,152 --> 00:34:01,560
There's a sick cat.

436
00:34:02,771 --> 00:34:04,313
So I stayed here and
watched over the cat with him.

437
00:34:04,337 --> 00:34:05,337
What?

438
00:34:05,564 --> 00:34:06,916
You stayed here with him?

439
00:34:08,490 --> 00:34:09,806
Not in the same bed,

440
00:34:10,299 --> 00:34:12,113
we just squeezed together on the floor.

441
00:34:12,241 --> 00:34:13,241
WHAT?!!!

442
00:34:13,334 --> 00:34:14,450
On the floor?

443
00:34:14,910 --> 00:34:15,910
Enough!

444
00:34:16,201 --> 00:34:17,935
Krapor is getting the wrong idea.

445
00:34:23,773 --> 00:34:25,061
There's really nothing going on.

446
00:34:25,445 --> 00:34:26,622
Come on. I'll walk you out.

447
00:34:27,217 --> 00:34:28,413
I've got something to ask you

448
00:34:29,442 --> 00:34:30,584
about the cats.

449
00:34:30,768 --> 00:34:32,928
But I want to ask you about
what happened on the floor.

450
00:34:33,043 --> 00:34:34,272
- See you.
- See you.

451
00:34:34,356 --> 00:34:35,156
Thank you.

452
00:34:35,277 --> 00:34:36,277
Have a nice day.

453
00:34:46,587 --> 00:34:47,587
John Wick.

454
00:34:51,177 --> 00:34:52,177
John Wick.

455
00:34:56,597 --> 00:34:57,597
John Wick.

456
00:34:59,630 --> 00:35:00,630
John Wick.

457
00:35:12,493 --> 00:35:13,493
Is everything alright?

458
00:35:13,553 --> 00:35:14,724
There's blood in the cat pee.

459
00:35:19,842 --> 00:35:20,842
John Wick's?

460
00:35:28,299 --> 00:35:29,299
John Wick.

461
00:35:29,499 --> 00:35:30,499
John Wick.

462
00:35:31,171 --> 00:35:32,171
John Wick.

463
00:35:34,667 --> 00:35:35,667
Have you found him?

464
00:35:35,928 --> 00:35:39,432
Nah. I looked everywhere, even outside.

465
00:35:41,119 --> 00:35:42,289
This place isn't that big.

466
00:35:42,495 --> 00:35:43,516
Where else could he hide?

467
00:35:46,989 --> 00:35:47,989
John Wick.

468
00:35:51,213 --> 00:35:54,517
Jiro, if you were John Wick,

469
00:35:55,385 --> 00:35:56,385
where would you hide?

470
00:35:56,484 --> 00:35:58,700
In this house,

471
00:35:59,064 --> 00:36:03,501
there's only one spot that's truly safe.

472
00:36:05,311 --> 00:36:06,311
Lynx.

473
00:36:07,259 --> 00:36:08,708
Have you checked your mom's room?

474
00:36:13,411 --> 00:36:14,797
This door knob doesn't work right.

475
00:36:15,092 --> 00:36:16,493
It opens if it gets bumped.

476
00:36:19,593 --> 00:36:22,623
I haven't been here since the funeral.

477
00:36:23,813 --> 00:36:24,907
It makes me think of her.

478
00:36:29,720 --> 00:36:30,720
Tiger.

479
00:36:31,098 --> 00:36:32,098
Blood.

480
00:36:36,070 --> 00:36:37,070
John Wick.

481
00:36:37,673 --> 00:36:38,673
John Wick.

482
00:36:39,871 --> 00:36:40,871
John Wick.

483
00:36:41,456 --> 00:36:42,456
John Wick.

484
00:36:42,506 --> 00:36:43,912
Tiger.
John Wick's under there.

485
00:36:44,629 --> 00:36:45,629
John Wick.

486
00:36:45,845 --> 00:36:46,845
John Wick.

487
00:36:49,190 --> 00:36:50,190
John Wick.

488
00:36:53,315 --> 00:36:54,625
Krapor told me this.

489
00:36:56,081 --> 00:36:57,617
My mom once found a cat at the temple

490
00:36:58,777 --> 00:37:00,017
while it was being attacked.

491
00:37:03,775 --> 00:37:04,775
Was that you, John Wick?

492
00:37:05,749 --> 00:37:06,967
It went under there.

493
00:37:07,107 --> 00:37:07,907
Where?

494
00:37:07,958 --> 00:37:09,252
Come out.

495
00:37:09,333 --> 00:37:10,373
Come out now!

496
00:37:11,603 --> 00:37:12,603
I'll be right back.

497
00:37:18,707 --> 00:37:19,707
John Wick.

498
00:37:19,774 --> 00:37:20,774
John Wick.

499
00:37:27,535 --> 00:37:28,625
- Come out.
- Get out of there.

500
00:37:28,657 --> 00:37:29,657
Come out!

501
00:37:30,633 --> 00:37:32,033
Where is it going?

502
00:37:33,089 --> 00:37:33,889
There.

503
00:37:33,946 --> 00:37:35,247
- Follow it.
- Where are you?

504
00:37:35,320 --> 00:37:36,520
Hey! What are you doing?

505
00:37:36,679 --> 00:37:38,531
Hey! Hurting a cat
brings bad karma, you know.

506
00:37:38,998 --> 00:37:40,021
You'll go to hell.

507
00:37:40,060 --> 00:37:41,544
Don't make me come at you.

508
00:37:42,128 --> 00:37:45,065
Meow, meow, meow. Come on out.

509
00:37:45,238 --> 00:37:46,734
You might get hurt if you stay there.

510
00:37:46,829 --> 00:37:47,865
Come here. Come on.

511
00:37:50,968 --> 00:37:52,305
I've got you. Ouch!

512
00:37:52,934 --> 00:37:53,934
Ouch!

513
00:38:00,648 --> 00:38:01,648
Ouch.

514
00:38:03,361 --> 00:38:04,361
Ouch!

515
00:38:05,828 --> 00:38:06,828
Ouch.

516
00:38:16,707 --> 00:38:17,744
Come here.

517
00:38:19,572 --> 00:38:21,061
I've got you now.

518
00:38:22,559 --> 00:38:23,701
Who scared you?

519
00:38:23,751 --> 00:38:24,751
Who?

520
00:38:26,409 --> 00:38:27,802
You're something, huh?

521
00:38:28,768 --> 00:38:30,808
I chased them all away.
Do you want to stay with me?

522
00:38:34,867 --> 00:38:35,867
John Wick.

523
00:38:37,708 --> 00:38:38,708
John Wick.

524
00:38:39,425 --> 00:38:40,642
You saw the monk, didn't you?

525
00:38:41,527 --> 00:38:42,730
It reminded you of the past.

526
00:38:44,857 --> 00:38:45,857
It's okay now.

527
00:38:46,778 --> 00:38:47,778
You're safe now.

528
00:38:51,061 --> 00:38:52,061
You're okay now.

529
00:38:52,796 --> 00:38:53,965
You're safe here, John Wick.

530
00:38:54,550 --> 00:39:00,821
♪ It feels so good now
with you by my side ♪

531
00:39:01,162 --> 00:39:05,786
♪ I'll hold you close, won't
let go, won't let it fade ♪

532
00:39:06,043 --> 00:39:10,901
♪ This warm and steady space you made ♪

533
00:39:10,973 --> 00:39:17,605
♪ 'Cause it's you, I found my home ♪

534
00:39:17,876 --> 00:39:20,057
Now we know the stress trigger,
it's easy to treat him.

535
00:39:20,649 --> 00:39:23,598
I think you should let him
stay over here today.

536
00:39:24,116 --> 00:39:25,637
He should be fine to go home tomorrow.

537
00:39:26,723 --> 00:39:27,810
Thank you, Dr. Pom.

538
00:39:28,752 --> 00:39:30,727
Ning, can you help bring the cat to rest?

539
00:39:30,811 --> 00:39:33,224
Got it. Come with me, John Wick.

540
00:39:37,090 --> 00:39:38,417
Come with me.

541
00:39:40,747 --> 00:39:43,157
I'm going home then.

542
00:39:46,417 --> 00:39:47,417
Wait.

543
00:39:54,136 --> 00:39:55,136
I'm not done yet.

544
00:39:57,051 --> 00:39:58,571
Come sit over here.

545
00:40:12,512 --> 00:40:13,512
It might sting a bit.

546
00:40:24,812 --> 00:40:26,514
Don't forget to get tetanus shots.

547
00:40:27,137 --> 00:40:29,780
You might get a slight fever
after the shots. Don't worry about it.

548
00:40:30,381 --> 00:40:31,381
Okay.

549
00:40:32,143 --> 00:40:35,426
I thought you once
said you didn't like cats.

550
00:40:36,194 --> 00:40:38,902
Now you've got cat scratches
all over your arms.

551
00:40:41,072 --> 00:40:43,804
I saw how scared John Wick was.

552
00:40:45,181 --> 00:40:46,594
So I thought if my mom were there,

553
00:40:47,560 --> 00:40:49,037
she'd do the same.

554
00:40:50,815 --> 00:40:51,815
Well done.

555
00:40:52,285 --> 00:40:53,618
You're really Je Meow's son.

556
00:41:01,438 --> 00:41:02,798
- Thank you for this.
- No worries.

557
00:41:14,403 --> 00:41:15,403
Hey.

558
00:41:16,235 --> 00:41:17,235
Hey, Lynx.

559
00:41:18,114 --> 00:41:19,114
We're back at the café.

560
00:41:25,161 --> 00:41:26,161
Let me help.

561
00:41:26,951 --> 00:41:28,684
It's alright. I can do it.

562
00:41:33,873 --> 00:41:35,005
Go get rest.

563
00:41:35,547 --> 00:41:36,804
You just got vaccinated.

564
00:41:37,593 --> 00:41:39,107
I'll take care of the cats for you.

565
00:41:39,774 --> 00:41:40,902
I can handle it just fine.

566
00:41:45,308 --> 00:41:47,002
When will you stop
being stubborn with me?

567
00:41:50,219 --> 00:41:52,408
I care about you no less than
the vet guy does.

568
00:41:53,471 --> 00:41:54,624
- Come on.
- Why?

569
00:41:55,057 --> 00:41:56,354
Do I have to scold you

570
00:41:57,582 --> 00:41:58,730
before you'll listen to me?

571
00:42:42,212 --> 00:42:43,212
Sorry.

572
00:43:13,201 --> 00:43:14,201
I'm sorry.

573
00:43:17,066 --> 00:43:19,207
Dr. Pom is like a big brother to me.

574
00:43:23,368 --> 00:43:24,906
He used to come by a lot.

575
00:43:25,304 --> 00:43:27,312
I'd always go to him when I need advice.

576
00:43:29,252 --> 00:43:30,516
But with you, I…

577
00:43:32,088 --> 00:43:33,455
I feel bad bothering you, I guess.

578
00:43:34,394 --> 00:43:36,111
If you let me be your kids' dad,

579
00:43:37,362 --> 00:43:38,946
then stop thinking you're bothering me.

580
00:43:40,224 --> 00:43:41,224
Understand?

581
00:43:56,388 --> 00:43:57,621
After finishing this,

582
00:43:58,220 --> 00:43:59,232
go lie down and rest.

583
00:43:59,685 --> 00:44:00,783
I'll take care of the cats.

584
00:44:48,744 --> 00:44:49,744
Please excuse me.

585
00:45:51,930 --> 00:45:53,220
You did really well today.

586
00:46:25,408 --> 00:46:27,006
Even cats choose

587
00:46:28,898 --> 00:46:30,513
who they let touch them, right?

588
00:46:32,301 --> 00:46:33,485
- Ouch.
- Lynx!

589
00:46:34,667 --> 00:46:35,667
You okay?

590
00:46:38,347 --> 00:46:39,365
Do you have a fever?

591
00:46:45,653 --> 00:46:47,697
I care about you no less than
the vet guy does.

592
00:47:21,377 --> 00:47:23,208
(Next Episode)
- Lynx. - Hi, Dr. Pom.

593
00:47:23,326 --> 00:47:24,644
I was just out running
around here with Gong Yoo.

594
00:47:24,668 --> 00:47:25,673
(Saranghaeyo.)

595
00:47:25,753 --> 00:47:27,634
(Here comes some refreshment!)

596
00:47:28,849 --> 00:47:31,415
You're all wet. Come upstairs.
I'll lend you some clothes.

597
00:47:31,480 --> 00:47:33,211
What about that one? I think I can wear it.

598
00:47:33,333 --> 00:47:34,373
It's Tiger's.

599
00:47:35,293 --> 00:47:37,920
He might have a crush on me.

600
00:47:38,344 --> 00:47:39,675
Maybe you try copying cats.

601
00:47:39,858 --> 00:47:43,215
Only the favorite cat near you
will know when your scent changes.

602
00:47:43,720 --> 00:47:45,005
Why did you change your perfume?

603
00:47:46,322 --> 00:47:47,523
I like the old one more.
